<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>For Ahsan 🤍</title>
<style>
body {
  background: #ffe6f0;
  text-align: center;
  font-family: Arial;
  padding: 50px;
}
h1 {
  color: #ff4d88;
}
p {
  font-size: 18px;
  color: #333;
  white-space: pre-line;
}
button {
  background: #ff4d88;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  font-size: 16px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
.hidden {
  display: none;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<h1>hey Ahsan... I made this for you 🤍</h1>

<p>click below... only if you promise not to laugh</p>

<button onclick="showMessage()">click me</button>

<p id="message" class="hidden">
i do not know how to say this Ahsan
without breaking the quiet between us
but you live somewhere in me
not loudly
not like a storm
more like a promise that never asked to be made
i like you
in a way that feels like standing guard
like i could be your shield
even when you do not believe you need one
you look at love like it is something that leaves
like every hand that holds you is temporary
like every warmth has an ending hidden inside it
and i wish i could take that fear out of you
hold it in my own chest instead
because what i feel is not passing
it is not a moment
it does not flicker when things get heavy
i am not here to go
i am not another story that will stop halfway
if you let me
i will stay in the quiet parts
in the days that feel empty
in the nights that remind you of everything you lost
i will stay
not loudly
not perfectly
but truly
and without leaving 🤍
</p>

<script>
function showMessage() {
  document.getElementById("message").classList.remove("hidden");
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
